Something wonderful happened to me the other week. 

I made my trudge down to my postbox to pick up, let’s be honest, what’s usually just bills and junk mail... but that day, I found something magical. A letter! ✉️ For me! 

You see, one of the ‘just because’ cards I have sent since this whole debacle began had received a response. A lovely, handwritten letter. 

I had a smile on my face all day long. My morning was busy so I saved it until later that day. I sat down to read it with a cup of tea, so I could give it some time and attention. The smile stayed all the way through...

This wasn’t a letter sent to tell me something significant or important, just filled with the kind of chat and reflections you share with someone you see every day. The stuff you wouldn’t think to text, and probably wouldn’t remember to mention on a catch up call. Just the little things that make up a day and a life. It was perfect.

Weeks later, I’m still thinking about it! 

Wouldn’t you love to have a moment like that, and give one too? Take some time this weekend to write to someone. It doesn’t matter what you say. Just pick up a pen, scribble a thought or two, pop it in the post and wait for something to come back to you. It will make yours and someone else’s day. Try it and see! 

